children.subject: I'm not certain about the workload for the other 3 classes, but I took EECS151 last semester and the workload for lecture is aight, but the workload for the lab was heavy (some weeks during the end of the semester spending ~ >25 hours in lab) .

history.content:
That sounds like a very heavy workload to me.  As your colleague indicated, 151 has a very substantial lab and more importantly final project component. 140 also has a lab and project, and although they may not be quite as time consuming as 151, it definitely isn't a light load either.  I'm not familiar with the load for 176, but 126 most likely wouldn't be as bad as the previous two in terms of sustained workload, however it can be a conceptually very challenging course, and so you'd to make sure you have enough time to assimilate that material as well.

Long story short - while I don't think this is absolutely impossible, this does sound like a pretty crazy schedule.  If you'd like, I'd be happy to sit down with you and chat about your course/career plans to see what some alternatives might look like/whether you really need to attempt this schedule - just send me a note.

Is EE 126, EECS 151, EE 140 and CS 176 for fall semester doable?

Thanks.
